content.description: The crux is about 12 feet off the ground, stepping out of the crack onto a sloping ramp. It can be dirty, and its getting pretty polished. It is however one of the few real beginners climbs in Iowa.
content.location: At the top, facing the river this climb is under the anchors on the left. Facing the rock, it is the climb on the right. When its dry you can walk down river past the Gazebo, down the stairs and walk to the climb next to the river. Most of the time you need to rappel down.

content.description: Facing the rock this is the climb on the left over small ledges and pockets.  Its pretty burley near the bottom. To make it really hard, start on the blank spot in the middle and see if you can pull through.
content.location: This route is next to Nanda Herring. Facing the rock its to the left. Facing the river it is under the top rope anchors on the right.

content.description: Near the Gazebo and a little upstream is an outcropping of rock on the other side of the fence.  There are two sets of top rope anchors there.
